    "The Cloud-Edge Continuum relies on diverse energy driven models, including brown energy model driven by grid power (electricity) for a reliable and uninterrupted power supply, green energy model driven by renewable energy sources such as solar and wind power, battery power for providing backup and sustained service during grid outages, and hybrid energy models that combine multiple energy sources to enhance reliability and efficiency.",
    "These energy models ensure uninterrupted operation, reducing carbon footprint, and optimize energy efficiency within the Cloud-Edge Continuum.",
